{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pfeffernüsse","content":["Place molasses, honey and butter into mixing bowl and heat <b>7 min\/80°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl and allow to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place all remaining pfeffernüsse ingredients, except eggs, into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add eggs and reserved honey and molasses mixture and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Wrap dough in plastic wrap or a silicone bread mat, then place in refrigerator for a minimum 2 hours or overnight. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 160°C. Line 2 baking trays (40 x 35 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Take 2 teaspoons of the dough at a time and roll into balls (approx. 47). Arrange balls on prepared baking trays 4 cm apart and press down on each ball to flatten slightly.","Bake for 10-12 minutes (160°C), then transfer onto a wire rack and allow to cool."]},{"title":"Glaze","content":["Place sugar in mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add rum (optional) and water and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Place pfeffernüsse onto a sheet of baking paper then, using a pastry brush, spread glaze onto the top of each biscuit. Serve immediately or transfer into a sealable storage container to store until use."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pfeffernüsse","content":["150 g molasses","70 g honey","90 g butter","550 g plain flour","150 g white sugar","80 g brown sugar","1 ½ tsp ground cardamom","1 tsp ground nutmeg","1 tsp ground cloves","1 tsp ground ginger","2 tsp ground cinnamon","1 ½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 tsp ground black pepper","½ tsp sea salt","2 eggs"]},{"title":"Glaze","content":["280 g icing sugar","1 tbsp rum              (optional)","30 g hot water"]}],"id":"r90150","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-x2NC35CLUy4\/XZWpruNjnsI\/AAAAAAAAfNc\/Qb4m5As-5k8wit0S06b3vGN0UPj_u8cmgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2Axo92urHdAZJhUt.png","title":"Pfeffernüsse (German spice biscuits)","p